column5: That was chicagos game in regulation had that goal not been disallowed, I think the integrity of the reffing this season is dwindling with quotes like this "He said his intention was to blow the whistle"  So without blowing the whistle the play can be called dead? just like the game 7 disallowed goal on Chicago again against the Red Wings. Luckily Seabrook saved them.
Chicago in six as predicted, lol, for my prize I choose a fly in to any of Mike's awesome destinations.  Seriously, great final between two teams with an amazing amount of grit!
